  GameRules: 'Three Card Brag Rules:

    

    1. Each player is dealt 3 cards
    at the start of each round.

    2. Players can bet blind or see their hand.

    3.
    Blind betting doubles the current bet.

    4. Players who have seen their hand
    bet double the current bet.

    5. Players can draw a new card to the floor.

    6.
    Players can pick and swap a card from the floor.

    7. Players can fold, call,
    or raise.

    8. Highest hand value wins (Ace high).

    9. In case of a
    tie, the highest card wins.

    10. The game ends when a player runs out of
    coins or after a set number of rounds.

    11. The trailing player can continue
    if they have more coins.

    12. Players start with 1000 coins.

'
  GameDescription: "Three Card Brag is an exciting card game that combines elements
    of poker and bluffing.\r\n Players aim to make the best three-card hand while
    betting and bluffing their way to victory.\r\nMost interesting part is we will
    be playing against Large language model LLM i.e Chat GPT "
  StrategyTips: "- Pay attention to your opponents' betting patterns.\r\n Use the
    blind betting option strategically to bluff or build the pot.\r\n Consider the
    odds of improving your hand when deciding to draw or swap cards.\r\n Don't be
    afraid to fold if you have a weak hand and the bets are high.\r\n Manage your
    coins wisely to stay in the game for multiple rounds."
